HEADWORD: Lif
<hw>Lif</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>lief</ets>.]</ety> <def>The fiber by which the petioles of the date
palm are bound together, from which various kinds of cordage are
made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

